message: From: http://lanyrd.com/2011/sxsw/scqxk/ "Programs like Y Combinator have garnered much attention in the media. Many of the startups are highlighted and critiqued upon launch, but how do these programs fare over time? What lessons have graduates of Y Combinator learned in a post-Y Combinator world? How do they turn ideas into real businesses?"
This looks like it'll be very cool. I'm curious what life's going to be like after YC!
I'm pointing to a YC startup's description from this YC startup's site to a panel on YC startups.  For bonus points, I found the original article on Hacker News.  I get the meta award for today.
I can't attend this but would love to see if someone attending (or on the panel) could share insights here.
